{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "07", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "12", "M": "53", "S": "41"}}, "news": [{"title": "Ahmedabad: Three construction sites in Gota sealed for not installing green nets", "para": "Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation has sealed three major construction sites in Gota for failing to install mandatory green nets and barricades. Additionally, a \u20b91 lakh fine was imposed on one site for material spillage onto public roads, while other sites faced penalties for pollution and safety violations. Encroachments were also cleared to improve traffic flow.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ahmedabads-crackdown-on-construction-sites-three-sealed-for-violating-dust-control-regulations/130080144?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-55086/130080144.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Residents of Secunderabad Cantonment Board seek reduction in transfer of property tax to 1.5%", "para": "Secunderabad Cantonment residents are protesting a 5% property tax rate set in 1989, arguing it's outdated and lacks public consultation. They demand a fresh notification, transparent objection process, and a reduction to 1.5%, aligning with GHMC rates. The Cantonment Vikas Manch highlights the need for fairness and democratic principles in tax imposition.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/residents-of-secunderabad-cantonment-board-seek-reduction-in-transfer-of-property-tax-to-1-5/130080100?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-96144/130080100.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Retail leasing dips to 1.95 million sq ft in Q1 2026 amid supply constraints: Report", "para": "Retail leasing across India\u2019s top cities declined in Q1 2026 due to lack of new supply, even as demand remained steady. Malls gained share amid rising preference for organised retail, while Delhi-NCR, Hyderabad and Mumbai led leasing activity.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/retail/retail-leasing-dips-to-1-95-million-sq-ft-in-q1-2026-amid-supply-constraints-report/130080613?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-194718/130080613.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "retail"}]}